  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean ears?",
  "response": "Here are some safe methods for cleaning ears:\n\n1. Gentle external cleaning\n- Use a soft, damp washcloth to clean the outer ear\n- Avoid inserting anything into the ear canal\n\n2. Recommended ear cleaning techniques\n- Tilt head and use ear drops to soften wax\n- Gently irrigate with warm water using a bulb syringe\n- Use over-the-counter ear drops designed for wax removal\n\n3. What to avoid\n- Cotton swabs/Q-tips (can push wax deeper or damage eardrum)\n- Sharp objects\n- Excessive cleaning\n\n4. When to seek professional help\n- Excessive ear wax buildup\n- Ear pain or discomfort\n- Hearing loss\n- Persistent ear problems\n\n5. Medical professional recommendations\n- Most people's ears are self-cleaning\n- Wax naturally moves out of the ear canal\n- Only clean ears if experiencing discomfort or reduced hearing\n\n6. Alternative methods\n- Hydrogen peroxide solution\n- Mineral or baby oil\n- Commercial ear cleaning kits\n\nAlways be gentle and cautious when cleaning ears to prevent potential damage or infection.",
